<text top="1020" left="1759" width="497" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t92" reading_order_no="85" segment_no="7" tag_type="text">ers  (PLCs)  traditionally  used  for </text>
<text top="1059" left="1759" width="440" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t93" reading_order_no="86" segment_no="7" tag_type="text">plant  control  do  not  offer  the </text>
<text top="1098" left="1759" width="424" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t94" reading_order_no="87" segment_no="7" tag_type="text">high-speed  I/O  required  for </text>
<text top="1138" left="1760" width="494" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t95" reading_order_no="88" segment_no="7" tag_type="text">diagnosis  and  monitoring  tasks. </text>
<text top="1178" left="1759" width="377" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t96" reading_order_no="89" segment_no="7" tag_type="text">In  contrast,  a  USB-based </text>
