<text top="1732" left="1759" width="408" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t110" reading_order_no="103" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">(HMIs)  with  USB  ports  are </text>
<text top="1772" left="1759" width="146" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t111" reading_order_no="104" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">available. </text>
<text top="1811" left="1799" width="367" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t112" reading_order_no="105" segment_no="9" tag_type="text">Since  its  release  in  1996, </text>
<text top="1851" left="1759" width="456" height="41" font="font3" id="p1_t113" reading_order_no="106" segment_no="9" tag_type="text">USB  has  become  the  standard </text>
